# PokéAPI Data Layer

- All PokéAPI fetch functions live in `lib/pokeapi.ts`
- API base URL: always use `POKEAPI_BASE_URL` from `lib/constants.ts` — never hardcode the URL
- TypeScript interfaces for API responses are colocated in `lib/pokeapi.ts`
- Type effectiveness engine (`lib/typeEffectiveness.ts`) — pure functions, no side effects, no fetch calls
- FRLG overrides: `lib/frlg-type-overrides.ts` maps Pokémon IDs to corrected Gen III types; `lib/frlg-pokemon.ts` lists valid FRLG IDs
- Always `throw` on non-ok fetch responses; callers are responsible for catching errors
- Helper functions (`formatDexNumber`, `getEnglishFlavorText`, `getFrlgSprite`) are in `lib/pokeapi.ts`
